<h3>Kexi - Database Creation For Everyone</h3>


<h3>Welcome</h3>
<p>Kexi is under active development. This document is to keep you informed about state of the project.</p>
<p>Current Kexi version is <b>Beta3</b>.</p>


<h3>What's new </h3>
<p>Changes since Beta2:
<ul>
<li>Improved Table Designer</li>
<li>Properties window added (now used for table designer, more to come)
<li>Consistent window closing, data saving, removing, editing, consistent questions</li>
<li>Table designs (and other design types, in the future) are now saved only when needed, on demand</li>
<li>Renewed Query Designer</li>
<li>&quot;Data&quot; menu added, with possibility of saving current table row</li>
</ul>
</p>


<h3>Additional functions</h3>
<p>
Following, not yet stable functions are provided for your information.
These are disabled by default after Kexi installation.
<ul>
<li>Form designer. To enable this function, select &quot;Settings-&gt;Other-&gt;Enable Forms&quot; menu</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Restrictions in this version</h3>
<p>
<ul>
<li>File-based projects are only supported</li>
<li>Table designer works only for new designs, altering existing table not available</li>
<li>Queries: saving, computing totals, setting criterias is temporary not available. 
Execution works without joining.</li>
</ul>
</p>

<!-- h2>Notes</h2 -->
